This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image denoising techniques. It also involves the use of machine learning-based methods, which suggests that it could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of convolutional neural networks (CNN) indicates that it could belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the iterative nature of the proposed method suggests that it could also belong to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category.
